content.text:
Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. The RichTextEditor uses `color="var(--accent-purple)"` for its BarLoader -- that is the established pattern. The `--loader-color` variable is also available (set to `#C4943E` in light mode and `#D4A853` in dark mode). Let me now produce the complete implementation plan.

---

## Detailed Implementation Plan: ProfilePage Editor UI Enhancement

This plan is organized into 6 files, addressed in dependency order. Each section contains the exact changes needed, why they are needed, and the specific code to write.

---

### Phase 1: Bug Fixes (highest priority, foundational)

---

#### FILE 1: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\ProfilePage\MyProfile.jsx`

This file contains 5 of the 9 bugs and is the parent orchestrator for all profile editing state.

**Change 1 -- Fix typo `opendRichTextEditor` (Bug #3)**

On line 85, rename the function from `opendRichTextEditor` to `openRichTextEditor`. Also update the reference on line 389 where it is passed to `<WriteJournalButton onOpen={opendRichTextEditor} />`.

```jsx
// Line 85: Before
const opendRichTextEditor = () => {
    setShowEditor(true);
};

// Line 85: After
const openRichTextEditor = () => {
    setShowEditor(true);
};

// Line 389: Before
<WriteJournalButton onOpen={opendRichTextEditor} />

// Line 389: After
<WriteJournalButton onOpen={openRichTextEditor} />
```

**Change 2 -- Fix typo `hancleClickCancelFontSelect` (Bug #2)**

On line 287, rename from `hancleClickCancelFontSelect` to `handleClickCancelFontSelect`. Also update the reference on line 310 where it is passed as a prop.

```jsx
// Line 287: Before
const hancleClickCancelFontSelect = () => {

// Line 287: After
const handleClickCancelFontSelect = () => {

// Line 310: Before
hancleClickCancelFontSelect={hancleClickCancelFontSelect}

// Line 310: After
handleClickCancelFontSelect={handleClickCancelFontSelect}
```

**Change 3 -- Fix cancel resetting font color to empty string (Bug #9)**

On line 289 inside the cancel handler, instead of `setFontColor("")`, revert to the last saved value from `userData`.

```jsx
// Line 287-290: Before
const hancleClickCancelFontSelect = () => {
    setShowFontColorSelector(false);
    setFontColor("");
};

// After
const handleClickCancelFontSelect = () => {
    setShowFontColorSelector(false);
    setFontColor(userData?.profile_font_color || "");
};
```

**Change 4 -- Remove duplicate `setProfileEditAvatar(file)` (Bug #5)**

On lines 121 and 123, the same call appears twice. Remove line 121.

```jsx
// Lines 119-133: Before
const handleImageOnChange = (e) => {
    const file = e.target.files[0];
    setProfileEditAvatar(file);
    if (file) {
        setProfileEditAvatar(file);
        // ...

// After
const handleImageOnChange = (e) => {
    const file = e.target.files[0];
    if (file) {
        setProfileEditAvatar(file);
        // ...
    } else {
        setProfileEditAvatar(null);
        setEditImagePreview("");
    }
};
```

Note: Also moved `setProfileEditAvatar(null)` into the else branch for clarity, since when no file is selected, the avatar should be null.

**Change 5 -- Add error state and user-visible error feedback (Bug #8)**

Add a new state variable for error messages. Modify all three save handlers to set a visible error message instead of silently throwing. Add an auto-clearing timeout.

```jsx
// After line 60 (existing state declarations), add:
const [saveError, setSaveError] = useState("");

// Add a helper to show and auto-clear errors:
const showError = useCallback((message) => {
    setSaveError(message);
    setTimeout(() => setSaveError(""), 4000);
}, []);
```

Then modify the three save handlers:

For `handleSaveProfileEdit` (line 155):
```jsx
// Line 181: Before
} catch {
    throw new Error("error saving update");
} finally {

// After
} catch {
    showError("Failed to save profile. Please try again.");
    return;
} finally {
```

Note: Move the `setIsSavingProfile(false)` and cleanup logic so that on error, we stop the loading state and show the error, but do NOT close the modal. The `finally` block currently closes the modal (`setShowProfileEditor(false)`) even on error. Restructure to:

```jsx
const handleSaveProfileEdit = async () => {
    setIsSavingProfile(true);
    setSaveError("");
    const data = { /* ... same ... */ };

    try {
        const formdata = new FormData();
        /* ... same FormData logic ... */
        await updateProfileData(formdata, session?.access_token);
        setProfileEditAvatar(null);
        queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["userData"] });
        setShowProfileEditor(false);
    } catch {
        showError("Failed to save profile. Please try again.");
    } finally {
        setIsSavingProfile(false);
    }
};
```

For `handleSaveProfileConfig` (line 191), same pattern:
```jsx
const handleSaveProfileConfig = async () => {
    setIsUpdatingProfileConfig(true);
    setSaveError("");
    try {
        if (imageSrc) {
            const croppedImageUrl = await getCroppedImage(imageSrc, croppedAreaPixels, userData.id, session?.access_token);
            if (croppedImageUrl) {
                setCroppedImage({ /* ... same ... */ });
            }
        } else if (gradientPicked) {
            setCroppedImage(gradientPicked);
        }
        setGradientPicked(null);
        setImageSrc(null);
        setShowBgPicker(false);
        queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["userData"] });
    } catch {
        showError("Failed to update background. Please try again.");
    } finally {
        setIsUpdatingProfileConfig(false);
    }
};
```

For `handleClickSaveFontColor` (line 272), same pattern:
```jsx
const handleClickSaveFontColor = async () => {
    setIsUpdatingFont(true);
    setSaveError("");
    const formdata = new FormData();
    formdata.append("fontColor", fontColor);
    try {
        await updateFontColor(session?.access_token, formdata);
        queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ["userData"] });
        setShowFontColorSelector(false);
    } catch {
        showError("Failed to update font color. Please try again.");
    } finally {
        setIsUpdatingFont(false);
    }
};
```

Pass `saveError` and `setSaveError` down to the child components that need it. Add the error toast JSX at the top of the return block:

```jsx
// In the return, before <ProfileFontColorSelector ...>, add:
{saveError && (
    <div className="profile-save-error-toast">
        {saveError}
    </div>
)}
```

---

#### FILE 2: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\ProfilePage\myprofile.css`

This file contains 2 bugs and needs all the new desktop overlay styling.

**Change 1 -- Add desktop `.profile-editor-bg` styles (Bug #1)**

Currently `.profile-editor-bg` only exists inside `@media (max-width: 428px)` and `@media (max-width: 480px)`. Add the base (desktop) rule. Use the same pattern as the working `.profile-layout-builder-bg` (line 484-493 of the same file).

Insert this before the mobile `@media` sections (e.g., after line 946, after the `.profile-edit-save-bttn:active` rule):

```css
/* ── Desktop overlay for profile edit modal ── */
.profile-editor-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    background-color: var(--bg-backdrop);
    backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
    z-index: 135;
}
```

This uses `var(--bg-backdrop)` and `backdrop-filter: blur(5px)` -- the exact same pattern as `profile-layout-builder-bg` at line 484.

**Change 2 -- Fix typo `canvel-save-container` (Bug #4)**

On line 119, rename from `.canvel-save-container` to `.cancel-save-container`.

```css
/* Line 119: Before */
.canvel-save-container{

/* After */
.cancel-save-container{
```

**Change 3 -- Add input focus ring for better visual feedback**

After the `.edit-profile-input:focus` rule (line 866-868), add a subtle border highlight:

```css
.edit-profile-input-name-container:focus-within {
    border-color: var(--accent-dark);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
}

.edit-profile-input-bio-container:focus-within {
    border-color: var(--accent-dark);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
}
```

**Change 4 -- Add save button disabled state**

```css
.profile-edit-save-bttn.is-saving {
    opacity: 0.6;
    cursor: not-allowed;
    pointer-events: none;
}
```

**Change 5 -- Add error toast styling**

Following the existing `repost-toast` pattern from `postcards.css`:

```css
.profile-save-error-toast {
    position: fixed;
    bottom: 2rem;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    z-index: 200;
    padding: 0.55rem 1.2rem;
    background: var(--color-danger);
    color: #fff;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    animation: profile-toast-in 0.3s ease-out;
}

@keyframes profile-toast-in {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(10px); }
    to { opacity: 1; transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(0); }
}
```

**Change 6 -- Add selected gradient indicator style**

```css
.gradient-box.gradient-selected {
    outline: 2.5px solid var(--accent-dark);
    outline-offset: 2px;
    transform: scale(1.08);
}
```

**Change 7 -- Enlarge font color swatch and add hex display area**

```css
.input-color {
    /* Update existing: change width/height from 50px to 60px */
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    border-radius: 12px; /* change from 50% to rounded square */
    border: 2px solid var(--border-light);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
}

.input-color:hover {
    transform: scale(1.05);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
}

.font-color-hex-label {
    font-family: "Lexend Deca", sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}
```

Also increase the `.font-selector-container` height from `120px` to `auto` (or `fit-content`) to accommodate the hex label:

```css
.font-selector-container {
    /* Change height from 120px to fit-content */
    height: fit-content;
}
```

---

#### FILE 3: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\ProfilePage\components\ProfileEditModal.jsx`

**Change 1 -- Fix BarLoader color from blue to warm accent (Bug #6)**

Line 158: Replace `color="rgb(40, 115, 255)"` with `color="var(--accent-purple)"` to match the established pattern used in RichTextEditor.jsx (line 111) and ChapterEditor.jsx (line 184).

```jsx
// Before
<BarLoader width={"100%"} loading={isSavingProfile} color="rgb(40, 115, 255)" speedMultiplier={0.7} />

// After
<BarLoader width={"100%"} loading={isSavingProfile} color="var(--accent-purple)" speedMultiplier={0.7} />
